                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/973a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-16T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 16, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Ecuadoran Minister has informed the Department that he understands that the
                    Ecuadoran Government resumed deposits upon Guayaquil &amp; Quito Railroad bonds
                    on August 8. Have you received any information to this effect from the Foreign
                    Office? If deposits have been resumed, cable Department manner of resumption,
                    exact amount, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
